ut choices to avoid optional modules.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying test setups and dependencies**\\n\\nI've been instructed to include environment variables, system properties, and test setup guidance in the agent guidance. It seems we won't take action unless extra setup is essential. If tests require YAML/JSON, using optional modules might introduce risks, so I'm thinking it’s best to note that. The core API should be reliable with MapPropertySource and similar properties. I'll need to ensure the current tests account for kotlin-reflect in the existing build.gradle, but it looks like 3.0.0.RC1 has the dependencies covered. Generally, the generated tests appear to include necessary resources without needing special setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"hoplite-core is self-contained for meaningful tests: its resolved artifact brings Kotlin reflect/stdlib and coroutines transitively, and core usage can exercise ConfigLoader, MapPropertySource/properties sources, preprocessors, and decoders without Docker, external services, environment variables, system properties, or optional Hoplite format modules.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Documentation notes that YAML/JSON/TOML/HOCON file formats require separate Hoplite modules, but those are optional format integrations and are not needed to cover hoplite-core itself; generated tests should avoid assuming those parsers are available unless testing a specific format artifact.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a2d5955533289bb016a40a93009a48197989a787b2811d138\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 8906, "output": 633, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27971, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1